CREATE TABLE user_profiles (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10)
);

CREATE TABLE music_preferences (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    genre VARCHAR(20),
    artist VARCHAR(50),
    favorite_songs VARCHAR[],
    last_updated TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE user_profiles (
  user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  age INT,
  location VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE user_preferences (
  user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  genre VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  language VARCHAR(50),
  mood VARCHAR(50),
  FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES user_profiles(user_id)
);

CREATE TABLE music_recommendations (
  recommendation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT,
  recommendation_text TEXT,
  recommendation_date DATE,
  FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES user_profiles(user_id)
);

CREATE TABLE user_profiles (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    first_name VARCHAR(50),
    last_name VARCHAR(50),
    email VARCHAR(100),
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10)
);

CREATE TABLE user_preferences (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    genre_preference VARCHAR(50),
    artist_preference VARCHAR(50),
    language_preference VARCHAR(50),
    tempo_preference VARCHAR(50),
    mood_preference VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE music_tracks (
    track_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    track_name VARCHAR(100),
    artist_name VARCHAR(100),
    genre VARCHAR(50),
    language VARCHAR(50),
    tempo VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE user_track_history (
    user_id INT,
    track_id INT,
    play_count INT,
    last_played TIMESTAMP,
    PRIMARY KEY (user_id, track_id)
);

CREATE TABLE user_profiles (
	user_id INT,
	username VARCHAR(50),
	email VARCHAR(100),
	date_of_birth DATE,
	PRIMARY KEY (user_id)
)

CREATE TABLE user_preferences (
	user_id INT,
	preference_id INT,
	genre VARCHAR(50),
	artist VARCHAR(100),
	song VARCHAR(100),
	PRIMARY KEY (user_id, preference_id),
	FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES user_profiles(user_id)
)

CREATE TABLE music_genres (
	genre_id INT,
	genre_name VARCHAR(50),
	PRIMARY KEY (genre_id)
)

CREATE TABLE artists (
	artist_id INT,
	artist_name VARCHAR(100),
	genre_id INT,
	PRIMARY KEY (artist_id),
	FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES music_genres(genre_id)
)

CREATE TABLE songs (
	song_id INT,
	song_name VARCHAR(100),
	artist_id INT,
	PRIMARY KEY (song_id),
	FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES artists(artist_id)
)
